Class AlphaBeta.StripedTranspositionTable

java.lang.Object
engine.forPlayer.forAI.AlphaBeta.StripedTranspositionTable
Enclosing class:
AlphaBeta
private static class AlphaBeta.StripedTranspositionTable extends Object
The StripedTranspositionTable class implements a thread-safe transposition table using striped locking to reduce contention in parallel search operations.
Author:
Aaron Ho

    • shouldReplace

      private boolean shouldReplace(TranspositionTable.Entry entry1, TranspositionTable.Entry entry2, int depth, byte nodeType)
      Determines which transposition table entry should be replaced based on depth, node type, and age criteria.
      Parameters:
      entry1 - The first entry candidate for replacement.
      entry2 - The second entry candidate for replacement.
      depth - The depth of the new entry.
      nodeType - The node type of the new entry.
      Returns:
      True if the first entry should be replaced, false for the second.
